The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Howrah crash kills 3 of wedding party
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Howrah crash kills 3 of wedding party
          A STAFF REPORTER                          The smashed car. Picture by Gopal Senapati                                   
	Calcutta, April 17: Three persons in a wedding party died when their car collided with a truck on the Delhi highway this evening.        
	Sanjiban Dutta, 32, a resident of Ramrajatala in Howrah, was on his way to wed Ishita Chatterjee of Uttarpara. The bor jatri (the grooms party) was travelling in three cars.        
	Sanjiban was in the first car. The second, a Maruti Omni, was hit by the speeding truck near Bally Halt station, 20km from here.         
	Driver Manoj Adhikary, 35, priest Prakita Chakraborty, 62, and barber Lakshman, 38, died before reaching hospital.         
	Three persons  Sanjibans father Sujit Kumar Dutta, the brides brother-in-law Gautam Ghoshal, and another relative of the bride, Shouvik Biswas  were injured. Gautam and Shouvik had gone to Ramrajatala to escort the grooms party.        
	The truck driver and his helper fled, leaving the vehicle behind, said Niraj Kumar Singh, superintendent of police, Howrah.         
	Residents rushed the six to Uttarpara State General Hospital, where Manoj, Prakita and Lakshman were declared dead on arrival. The other three were admitted with serious injuries.        
	We had just crossed Bally Halt station when there was a loud crash as a truck coming from the opposite direction hit us head-on, said Gautam from his hospital bed.         
	Pradip Sengupta, who saw the collision, said the accident took place on a stretch of the road where there was neither a divider nor any traffic personnel.         
	Sanjiban reached Uttarpara safe. The wedding rituals had begun when news of the accident came.         
	VIP Road accident        
	A Maruti Omni van turned turtle on VIP Road near Bangur Avenue around 10.30pm today. The driver was injured.                                                                                                                                                                          
